        {
            "block_label": "figure_title",
            "block_content": "<div style=\"text-align: center;\">Figure 3. Bottleneck analysis for Llama-2-7B on NVIDIA RTX 4090. Left: In on-device LLM applications, generation stage is much slower than the context stage. Middle: The generation stage is memory bound and has low arithmetic intensity. W4A16 quantization can effectively improve the arithmetic intensity by 4×. Right: The amount of weight access is orders of magnitude larger than the amount of activation access. Thus, weight-only quantization is more effective for on-device LLMs.</div>\n",
            "block_bbox": [
                105,
                350,
                1088,
                432
            ],
            "block_id": 7,
            "block_order": null,
            "group_id": 7,
